						<p>So if I half fill a bucket with water, and tie a rope to its handle whereby I start spinning it like an idiot around the house, will the water's center of mass be higher that it'd be were the bucket simply set on the floor in the same position? If so, what lifts the water uphill, the gays ?</p>
<p>If I buy one of those jewish toys which you spin, the kind that has lights and even maybe plays a noise <em>when spun</em> but takes no battery, who powers the circuitry, dead niggers ?</p>
<p>It'd seem that the centripetal force does in fact do ~some~ work, wouldn't it.</p>
